# .git-blame-ignore-revs
#
# Commits listed here are skipped by `git blame` because they are
# purely mechanical (reformat, mass codemod) and would otherwise hide
# the real author of each line under a rustfmt/clippy-fix signature.
#
# - GitHub's blame view reads this file automatically (no config needed).
# - Local CLI `git blame` respects it after:
#       git config --local blame.ignoreRevsFile .git-blame-ignore-revs
#
# Policy (see docs/git-blame-hygiene-in-ai-devflow.md):
#   - Only mechanical transformations go here: cargo fmt, clippy --fix,
#     codemod, mass rename, dependency bumps.
#   - Every entry uses the MERGE COMMIT SHA on `main` (this repo squash-
#     merges, so feature-branch SHAs do not exist on main).
#   - Each entry carries a 1-line comment with the PR number and the
#     tracking BL, so future readers understand why it is skipped.

